  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So you used to come back from-- from your place of work, and-- and you used to have to drag these bodies-- the ones-- we were able, still, to walk, had to drag the dead bodies with us, to bring them in into main camp.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know  if you realize that Birkenau had what they called 'eine kleine Postenkette' and a large Postenkette.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Meaning that, in the night, the camp was, to an extent, only around the barracks, with electric wires and towers with SS around the camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was called the 'kleine Postenkette'-- the small circle around that they had to watch.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "During the day, that expanded to such an extent that it was miles.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because every detail had to go out of the camp to work.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that become, all of a sudden, a much larger camp than it was before.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
